 36 // Next three methods are solely for IE5, which is missing them
 37 if (!Array.prototype.push) {
 38 	Array.prototype.push = function() {
 39         for (var i = 0, len = arguments.length; i < len; i++){
 40             this[this.length] = arguments[i];
 41         }
 42         return this.length;
 43 	};
 44 }
 45 
 46 if (!Array.prototype.shift) {
 47 	Array.prototype.shift = function() {
 48 		if (this.length > 0) {
 49 			var firstItem = this[0];
 50 			for (var i = 0, len = this.length - 1; i < len; i++) {
 51 				this[i] = this[i + 1];
 52 			}
 53 			this.length = this.length - 1;
 54 			return firstItem;
 55 		}
 56 	};
 57 }
 58 
 59 if (!Array.prototype.splice) {
 60 	Array.prototype.splice = function(startIndex, deleteCount) {
 61 		var itemsAfterDeleted = this.slice(startIndex + deleteCount);
 62 		var itemsDeleted = this.slice(startIndex, startIndex + deleteCount);
 63 		this.length = startIndex;
 64 		// Copy the arguments into a proper Array object
 65 		var argumentsArray = [];
 66 		for (var i = 0, len = arguments.length; i < len; i++) {
 67 			argumentsArray[i] = arguments[i];
 68 		}
 69 		var itemsToAppend = (argumentsArray.length > 2) ?
 70 			itemsAfterDeleted = argumentsArray.slice(2).concat(itemsAfterDeleted) : itemsAfterDeleted;
 71 		for (i = 0, len = itemsToAppend.length; i < len; i++) {
 72 			this.push(itemsToAppend[i]);
 73 		}
 74 		return itemsDeleted;
 75 	};
 76 }

 91 	function EventSupport() {}
 92 
 93 	EventSupport.prototype = {
 94 		eventTypes: [],
 95 		eventListeners: {},
 96 		setEventTypes: function(eventTypesParam) {
 97 			if (eventTypesParam instanceof Array) {
 98 				this.eventTypes = eventTypesParam;
 99 				this.eventListeners = {};
100 				for (var i = 0, len = this.eventTypes.length; i < len; i++) {
101 					this.eventListeners[this.eventTypes[i]] = [];
102 				}
103 			} else {
104 				handleError("log4javascript.EventSupport [" + this + "]: setEventTypes: eventTypes parameter must be an Array");
105 			}
106 		},
107 
108 		addEventListener: function(eventType, listener) {
109 			if (typeof listener == "function") {
110 				if (!array_contains(this.eventTypes, eventType)) {
111 					handleError("log4javascript.EventSupport [" + this + "]: addEventListener: no event called '" + eventType + "'");
112 				}
113 				this.eventListeners[eventType].push(listener);
114 			} else {
115 				handleError("log4javascript.EventSupport [" + this + "]: addEventListener: listener must be a function");
116 			}
117 		},
118 
119 		removeEventListener: function(eventType, listener) {
120 			if (typeof listener == "function") {
121 				if (!array_contains(this.eventTypes, eventType)) {
122 					handleError("log4javascript.EventSupport [" + this + "]: removeEventListener: no event called '" + eventType + "'");
123 				}
124 				array_remove(this.eventListeners[eventType], listener);
125 			} else {
126 				handleError("log4javascript.EventSupport [" + this + "]: removeEventListener: listener must be a function");
127 			}
128 		},
129 
130 		dispatchEvent: function(eventType, eventArgs) {
131 			if (array_contains(this.eventTypes, eventType)) {
132 				var listeners = this.eventListeners[eventType];
133 				for (var i = 0, len = listeners.length; i < len; i++) {
134 					listeners[i](this, eventType, eventArgs);
135 				}
136 			} else {
137 				handleError("log4javascript.EventSupport [" + this + "]: dispatchEvent: no event called '" + eventType + "'");
138 			}
139 		}
140 	};

181 	function getUrlFileName(url) {
182 		var lastSlashIndex = Math.max(url.lastIndexOf("/"), url.lastIndexOf("\\"));
183 		return url.substr(lastSlashIndex + 1);
184 	}

186 	// Returns a nicely formatted representation of an error
187 	function getExceptionStringRep(ex) {
188 		if (ex) {
189 			var exStr = "Exception: " + getExceptionMessage(ex);
190 			try {
191 				if (ex.lineNumber) {
192 					exStr += " on line number " + ex.lineNumber;
193 				}
194 				if (ex.fileName) {
195 					exStr += " in file " + getUrlFileName(ex.fileName);
196 				}
197 			} catch (localEx) {
198 				logLog.warn("Unable to obtain file and line information for error");
199 			}
200 			if (showStackTraces && ex.stack) {
201 				exStr += newLine + "Stack trace:" + newLine + ex.stack;
202 			}
203 			return exStr;
204 		}
205 		return null;
206 	}

230 	function array_remove(arr, val) {
231 		var index = -1;
232 		for (var i = 0, len = arr.length; i < len; i++) {
233 			if (arr[i] === val) {
234 				index = i;
235 				break;
236 			}
237 		}
238 		if (index >= 0) {
239 			arr.splice(index, 1);
240 			return true;
241 		} else {
242 			return false;
243 		}
244 	}
245 
246 	function array_contains(arr, val) {
247 		for(var i = 0, len = arr.length; i < len; i++) {
248 			if (arr[i] == val) {
249 				return true;
250 			}
251 		}
252 		return false;
253 	}

271 	function extractIntFromParam(param, defaultValue) {
272 		if (isUndefined(param)) {
273 			return defaultValue;
274 		} else {
275 			try {
276 				var value = parseInt(param, 10);
277 				return isNaN(value) ? defaultValue : value;
278 			} catch (ex) {
279 				logLog.warn("Invalid int param " + param, ex);
280 				return defaultValue;
281 			}
282 		}

297 	if (!Function.prototype.apply){
298 	    Function.prototype.apply = function(obj, args) {
299 	    	var methodName = "__apply__";
300 	    	if (typeof obj[methodName] != "undefined") {
301 	    		methodName += String(Math.random()).substr(2);
302 	    	}
303 	    	obj[methodName] = this;
304 
305 	    	var argsStrings = [];
306 	    	for (var i = 0, len = args.length; i < len; i++) {
307 	    		argsStrings[i] = "args[" + i + "]";
308 	    	}
309 	    	var script = "obj." + methodName + "(" + argsStrings.join(",") + ")";
310 	    	var returnValue = eval(script);
311 	    	delete obj[methodName];
312 	    	return returnValue;
313 	    };
314 	}

316 	if (!Function.prototype.call){
317 	    Function.prototype.call = function(obj) {
318 	    	var args = [];
319 	    	for (var i = 1, len = arguments.length; i < len; i++) {
320 	    		args[i - 1] = arguments[i];
321 	    	}
322 	        return this.apply(obj, args);
323 	    };
324 	}

326 	function getListenersPropertyName(eventName) {
327 		return "__log4javascript_listeners__" + eventName;
328 	}
329 
330 	function addEvent(node, eventName, listener, useCapture, win) {
331 		win = win ? win : window;
332 		if (node.addEventListener) {
333 			node.addEventListener(eventName, listener, useCapture);
334 		} else if (node.attachEvent) {
335 			node.attachEvent("on" + eventName, listener);
336 		} else {
337 			var propertyName = getListenersPropertyName(eventName);
338 			if (!node[propertyName]) {
339 				node[propertyName] = [];
340 				// Set event handler
341 				node["on" + eventName] = function(evt) {
342 					evt = getEvent(evt, win);
343 					var listenersPropertyName = getListenersPropertyName(eventName);
344 
345 					// Clone the array of listeners to leave the original untouched
346 					var listeners = this[listenersPropertyName].concat([]);
347 					var currentListener;
348 
349 					// Call each listener in turn
350 					while ((currentListener = listeners.shift())) {
351 						currentListener.call(this, evt);
352 					}
353 				};
354 			}
355 			node[propertyName].push(listener);
356 		}
357 	}
358 
359 	function removeEvent(node, eventName, listener, useCapture) {
360 		if (node.removeEventListener) {
361 			node.removeEventListener(eventName, listener, useCapture);
362 		} else if (node.detachEvent) {
363 			node.detachEvent("on" + eventName, listener);
364 		} else {
365 			var propertyName = getListenersPropertyName(eventName);
366 			if (node[propertyName]) {
367 				array_remove(node[propertyName], listener);
368 			}
369 		}
370 	}
371 
372 	function getEvent(evt, win) {
373 		win = win ? win : window;
374 		return evt ? evt : win.event;
375 	}

377 	function stopEventPropagation(evt) {
378 		if (evt.stopPropagation) {
379 			evt.stopPropagation();
380 		} else if (typeof evt.cancelBubble != "undefined") {
381 			evt.cancelBubble = true;
382 		}
383 		evt.returnValue = false;
384 	}

523 	var anonymousLoggerName = "[anonymous]";
524 	var defaultLoggerName = "[default]";
525 	var nullLoggerName = "[null]";
526 	var rootLoggerName = "root";
527 
528 	function Logger(name) {
529 		this.name = name;
530 		this.parent = null;
531 		this.children = [];
532 
533 		var appenders = [];
534 		var loggerLevel = null;
535 		var isRoot = (this.name === rootLoggerName);
536 		var isNull = (this.name === nullLoggerName);
537 
538 		var appenderCache = null;
539 		var appenderCacheInvalidated = false;
540 		
541 		this.addChild = function(childLogger) {
542 			this.children.push(childLogger);
543 			childLogger.parent = this;
544 			childLogger.invalidateAppenderCache();
545 		};
546 
547 		// Additivity
548 		var additive = true;
549 		this.getAdditivity = function() {
550 			return additive;
551 		};
552 
553 		this.setAdditivity = function(additivity) {
554 			var valueChanged = (additive != additivity);
555 			additive = additivity;
556 			if (valueChanged) {
557 				this.invalidateAppenderCache();
558 			}
559 		};
560 
561 		// Create methods that use the appenders variable in this scope
562 		this.addAppender = function(appender) {
563 			if (isNull) {
564 				handleError("Logger.addAppender: you may not add an appender to the null logger");
565 			} else {
566 				if (appender instanceof log4javascript.Appender) {
567 					if (!array_contains(appenders, appender)) {
568 						appenders.push(appender);
569 						appender.setAddedToLogger(this);
570 						this.invalidateAppenderCache();
571 					}
572 				} else {
573 					handleError("Logger.addAppender: appender supplied ('" +
574 						toStr(appender) + "') is not a subclass of Appender");
575 				}
576 			}
577 		};
578 
579 		this.removeAppender = function(appender) {
580 			array_remove(appenders, appender);
581 			appender.setRemovedFromLogger(this);
582 			this.invalidateAppenderCache();
583 		};
584 
585 		this.removeAllAppenders = function() {
586 			var appenderCount = appenders.length;
587 			if (appenderCount > 0) {
588 				for (var i = 0; i < appenderCount; i++) {
589 					appenders[i].setRemovedFromLogger(this);
590 				}
591 				appenders.length = 0;
592 				this.invalidateAppenderCache();
593 			}
594 		};
595 
596 		this.getEffectiveAppenders = function() {
597 			if (appenderCache === null || appenderCacheInvalidated) {
598 				// Build appender cache
599 				var parentEffectiveAppenders = (isRoot || !this.getAdditivity()) ?
600 					[] : this.parent.getEffectiveAppenders();
601 				appenderCache = parentEffectiveAppenders.concat(appenders);
602 				appenderCacheInvalidated = false;
603 			}
604 			return appenderCache;
605 		};
606 		
607 		this.invalidateAppenderCache = function() {
608 			appenderCacheInvalidated = true;
609 			for (var i = 0, len = this.children.length; i < len; i++) {
610 				this.children[i].invalidateAppenderCache();
611 			}
612 		};
613 
614 		this.log = function(level, params) {
615 			if (level.isGreaterOrEqual(this.getEffectiveLevel())) {
616 				// Check whether last param is an exception
617 				var exception;
618 				var finalParamIndex = params.length - 1;
619 				var lastParam = params[params.length - 1];
620 				if (params.length > 1 && isError(lastParam)) {
621 					exception = lastParam;
622 					finalParamIndex--;
623 				}
624 
625 				// Construct genuine array for the params
626 				var messages = [];
627 				for (var i = 0; i <= finalParamIndex; i++) {
628 					messages[i] = params[i];
629 				}
630 
631 				var loggingEvent = new LoggingEvent(
632 					this, new Date(), level, messages, exception);
633 
634 				this.callAppenders(loggingEvent);
635 			}
636 		};
637 
638 		this.callAppenders = function(loggingEvent) {
639 			var effectiveAppenders = this.getEffectiveAppenders();
640 			for (var i = 0, len = effectiveAppenders.length; i < len; i++) {
641 				effectiveAppenders[i].doAppend(loggingEvent);
642 			}
643 		};
644 
645 		this.setLevel = function(level) {
646 			// Having a level of null on the root logger would be very bad.
647 			if (isRoot && level === null) {
648 				handleError("Logger.setLevel: you cannot set the level of the root logger to null");
649 			} else if (level instanceof Level) {
650 				loggerLevel = level;
651 			} else {
652 				handleError("Logger.setLevel: level supplied to logger " +
653 					this.name + " is not an instance of log4javascript.Level");
654 			}
655 		};
656 
657 		this.getLevel = function() {
658 			return loggerLevel;
659 		};
660 
661 		this.getEffectiveLevel = function() {
662 			for (var logger = this; logger !== null; logger = logger.parent) {
663 				var level = logger.getLevel();
664 				if (level !== null) {
665 					return level;
666 				}
667 			}
668 		};
669 
670 		this.group = function(name, initiallyExpanded) {
671 			var effectiveAppenders = this.getEffectiveAppenders();
672 			for (var i = 0, len = effectiveAppenders.length; i < len; i++) {
673 				effectiveAppenders[i].group(name, initiallyExpanded);
674 			}
675 		};
676 
677 		this.groupEnd = function(name) {
678 			var effectiveAppenders = this.getEffectiveAppenders();
679 			for (var i = 0, len = effectiveAppenders.length; i < len; i++) {
680 				effectiveAppenders[i].groupEnd();
681 			}
682 		};
683 
684 		var timers = {};
685 
686 		this.time = function(name, level) {
687 			if (isUndefined(name)) {
688 				handleError("Logger.time: a name for the timer must be supplied");
689 			} else if (level && !(level instanceof Level)) {
690 				handleError("Logger.time: level supplied to timer " +
691 					name + " is not an instance of log4javascript.Level");
692 			} else {
693 				timers[name] = new Timer(name, level);
694 			}
695 		};

697 		this.timeEnd = function(name) {
698 			if (isUndefined(name)) {
699 				handleError("Logger.timeEnd: a name for the timer must be supplied");
700 			} else if (timers[name]) {
701 				var timer = timers[name];
702 				var milliseconds = timer.getElapsedTime();
703 				this.log(timer.level, ["Timer " + toStr(name) + " completed in " + milliseconds + "ms"]);
704 				delete timers[name];
705 			} else {
706 				logLog.warn("Logger.timeEnd: no timer found with name " + name);
707 			}
708 		};

710 		this.assert = function(expr) {
711 			if (!expr) {
712 				var args = [];
713 				for (var i = 1, len = arguments.length; i < len; i++) {
714 					args.push(arguments[i]);
715 				}
716 				args = (args.length > 0) ? args : ["Assertion Failure"];
717 				args.push(newLine);
718 				args.push(expr);
719 				this.log(Level.ERROR, args);
720 			}
721 		};

724 			return "Logger[" + this.name + "]";
725 		};
726 	}

804 	log4javascript.getLogger = function(loggerName) {
805 		// Use default logger if loggerName is not specified or invalid
806 		if (!(typeof loggerName == "string")) {
807 			loggerName = anonymousLoggerName;
808 			logLog.warn("log4javascript.getLogger: non-string logger name "	+
809 				toStr(loggerName) + " supplied, returning anonymous logger");
810 		}
811 
812 		// Do not allow retrieval of the root logger by name
813 		if (loggerName == rootLoggerName) {
814 			handleError("log4javascript.getLogger: root logger may not be obtained by name");
815 		}
816 
817 		// Create the logger for this name if it doesn't already exist
818 		if (!loggers[loggerName]) {
819 			var logger = new Logger(loggerName);
820 			loggers[loggerName] = logger;
821 			loggerNames.push(loggerName);
822 
823 			// Set up parent logger, if it doesn't exist
824 			var lastDotIndex = loggerName.lastIndexOf(".");
825 			var parentLogger;
826 			if (lastDotIndex > -1) {
827 				var parentLoggerName = loggerName.substring(0, lastDotIndex);
828 				parentLogger = log4javascript.getLogger(parentLoggerName); // Recursively sets up grandparents etc.
829 			} else {
830 				parentLogger = rootLogger;
831 			}
832 			parentLogger.addChild(logger);
833 		}
834 		return loggers[loggerName];
835 	};

1231 	JsonLayout.prototype.format = function(loggingEvent) {
1232 		var layout = this;
1233 		var dataValues = this.getDataValues(loggingEvent, this.combineMessages);
1234 		var str = "{" + this.lineBreak;
1235 		var i;
1236 		
1237 		function formatValue(val, prefix, expand) {
1238 			// Check the type of the data value to decide whether quotation marks
1239 			// or expansion are required
1240 			var formattedValue;
1241 			var valType = typeof val;
1242 			if (val instanceof Date) {
1243 				formattedValue = String(val.getTime());
1244 			} else if (expand && (val instanceof Array)) {
1245 				formattedValue = "[" + layout.lineBreak;
1246 				for (i = 0, len = val.length; i < len; i++) {
1247 					var childPrefix = prefix + layout.tab;
1248 					formattedValue += childPrefix + formatValue(val[i], childPrefix, false);
1249 					if (i < val.length - 1) {
1250 						formattedValue += ",";
1251 					}
1252 					formattedValue += layout.lineBreak;
1253 				}
1254 				formattedValue += prefix + "]";
1255 			} else if (valType !== "number" && valType !== "boolean") {
1256 				formattedValue = "\"" + escapeNewLines(toStr(val).replace(/\"/g, "\\\"")) + "\"";
1257 			} else {
1258 				formattedValue = val;
1259 			}
1260 			return formattedValue;
1261 		}
1262 		
1263 		for (i = 0, len = dataValues.length; i < len; i++) {
1264 			str += this.tab + "\"" + dataValues[i][0] + "\"" + this.colon + formatValue(dataValues[i][1], this.tab, true);
1265 			if (i < dataValues.length - 1) {
1266 				str += ",";
1267 			}
1268 			str += this.lineBreak;
1269 		}
1270 
1271 		str += "}" + this.lineBreak;
1272 		return str;
1273 	};

1327 	function formatObjectExpansion(obj, depth, indentation) {
1328 		var objectsExpanded = [];
1329 
1330 		function doFormat(obj, depth, indentation) {
1331 			var i, j, len, childDepth, childIndentation, childLines, expansion,
1332 				childExpansion;
1333 
1334 			if (!indentation) {
1335 				indentation = "";
1336 			}
1337 
1338 			function formatString(text) {
1339 				var lines = splitIntoLines(text);
1340 				for (var j = 1, jLen = lines.length; j < jLen; j++) {
1341 					lines[j] = indentation + lines[j];
1342 				}
1343 				return lines.join(newLine);
1344 			}
1345 
1346 			if (obj === null) {
1347 				return "null";
1348 			} else if (typeof obj == "undefined") {
1349 				return "undefined";
1350 			} else if (typeof obj == "string") {
1351 				return formatString(obj);
1352 			} else if (typeof obj == "object" && array_contains(objectsExpanded, obj)) {
1353 				try {
1354 					expansion = toStr(obj);
1355 				} catch (ex) {
1356 					expansion = "Error formatting property. Details: " + getExceptionStringRep(ex);
1357 				}
1358 				return expansion + " [already expanded]";
1359 			} else if ((obj instanceof Array) && depth > 0) {
1360 				objectsExpanded.push(obj);
1361 				expansion = "[" + newLine;
1362 				childDepth = depth - 1;
1363 				childIndentation = indentation + "  ";
1364 				childLines = [];
1365 				for (i = 0, len = obj.length; i < len; i++) {
1366 					try {
1367 						childExpansion = doFormat(obj[i], childDepth, childIndentation);
1368 						childLines.push(childIndentation + childExpansion);
1369 					} catch (ex) {
1370 						childLines.push(childIndentation + "Error formatting array member. Details: " +
1371 							getExceptionStringRep(ex) + "");
1372 					}
1373 				}
1374 				expansion += childLines.join("," + newLine) + newLine + indentation + "]";
1375 				return expansion;
1376 			} else if (typeof obj == "object" && depth > 0) {
1377 				objectsExpanded.push(obj);
1378 				expansion = "{" + newLine;
1379 				childDepth = depth - 1;
1380 				childIndentation = indentation + "  ";
1381 				childLines = [];
1382 				for (i in obj) {
1383 					try {
1384 						childExpansion = doFormat(obj[i], childDepth, childIndentation);
1385 						childLines.push(childIndentation + i + ": " + childExpansion);
1386 					} catch (ex) {
1387 						childLines.push(childIndentation + i + ": Error formatting property. Details: " +
1388 							getExceptionStringRep(ex));
1389 					}
1390 				}
1391 				expansion += childLines.join("," + newLine) + newLine + indentation + "}";
1392 				return expansion;
1393 			} else {
1394 				return formatString(toStr(obj));
1395 			}
1396 		}
1397 		return doFormat(obj, depth, indentation);
1398 	}

1538 		SimpleDateFormat.prototype.format = function(date) {
1539 			var formattedString = "";
1540 			var result;
1541 			var searchString = this.formatString;
1542 			while ((result = regex.exec(searchString))) {
1543 				var quotedString = result[1];
1544 				var patternLetters = result[2];
1545 				var otherLetters = result[3];
1546 				var otherCharacters = result[4];
1547 
1548 				// If the pattern matched is quoted string, output the text between the quotes
1549 				if (quotedString) {
1550 					if (quotedString == "''") {
1551 						formattedString += "'";
1552 					} else {
1553 						formattedString += quotedString.substring(1, quotedString.length - 1);
1554 					}
1555 				} else if (otherLetters) {
1556 					// Swallow non-pattern letters by doing nothing here
1557 				} else if (otherCharacters) {
1558 					// Simply output other characters
1559 					formattedString += otherCharacters;
1560 				} else if (patternLetters) {
1561 					// Replace pattern letters
1562 					var patternLetter = patternLetters.charAt(0);
1563 					var numberOfLetters = patternLetters.length;
1564 					var rawData = "";
1565 					switch(patternLetter) {
1566 						case "G":
1567 							rawData = "AD";
1568 							break;
1569 						case "y":
1570 							rawData = date.getFullYear();
1571 							break;
1572 						case "M":
1573 							rawData = date.getMonth();
1574 							break;
1575 						case "w":
1576 							rawData = date.getWeekInYear(this.getMinimalDaysInFirstWeek());
1577 							break;
1578 						case "W":
1579 							rawData = date.getWeekInMonth(this.getMinimalDaysInFirstWeek());
1580 							break;
1581 						case "D":
1582 							rawData = date.getDayInYear();
1583 							break;
1584 						case "d":
1585 							rawData = date.getDate();
1586 							break;
1587 						case "F":
1588 							rawData = 1 + Math.floor((date.getDate() - 1) / 7);
1589 							break;
1590 						case "E":
1591 							rawData = dayNames[date.getDay()];
1592 							break;
1593 						case "a":
1594 							rawData = (date.getHours() >= 12) ? "PM" : "AM";
1595 							break;
1596 						case "H":
1597 							rawData = date.getHours();
1598 							break;
1599 						case "k":
1600 							rawData = date.getHours() || 24;
1601 							break;
1602 						case "K":
1603 							rawData = date.getHours() % 12;
1604 							break;
1605 						case "h":
1606 							rawData = (date.getHours() % 12) || 12;
1607 							break;
1608 						case "m":
1609 							rawData = date.getMinutes();
1610 							break;
1611 						case "s":
1612 							rawData = date.getSeconds();
1613 							break;
1614 						case "S":
1615 							rawData = date.getMilliseconds();
1616 							break;
1617 						case "Z":
1618 							rawData = date.getTimezoneOffset(); // This returns the number of minutes since GMT was this time.
1619 							break;
1620 					}
1621 					// Format the raw data depending on the type
1622 					switch(types[patternLetter]) {
1623 						case TEXT2:
1624 							formattedString += formatText(rawData, numberOfLetters, 2);
1625 							break;
1626 						case TEXT3:
1627 							formattedString += formatText(rawData, numberOfLetters, 3);
1628 							break;
1629 						case NUMBER:
1630 							formattedString += formatNumber(rawData, numberOfLetters);
1631 							break;
1632 						case YEAR:
1633 							if (numberOfLetters <= 3) {
1634 								// Output a 2-digit year
1635 								var dataString = "" + rawData;
1636 								formattedString += dataString.substr(2, 2);
1637 							} else {
1638 								formattedString += formatNumber(rawData, numberOfLetters);
1639 							}
1640 							break;
1641 						case MONTH:
1642 							if (numberOfLetters >= 3) {
1643 								formattedString += formatText(monthNames[rawData], numberOfLetters, numberOfLetters);
1644 							} else {
1645 								// NB. Months returned by getMonth are zero-based
1646 								formattedString += formatNumber(rawData + 1, numberOfLetters);
1647 							}
1648 							break;
1649 						case TIMEZONE:
1650 							var isPositive = (rawData > 0);
1651 							// The following line looks like a mistake but isn't
1652 							// because of the way getTimezoneOffset measures.
1653 							var prefix = isPositive ? "-" : "+";
1654 							var absData = Math.abs(rawData);
1655 
1656 							// Hours
1657 							var hours = "" + Math.floor(absData / 60);
1658 							hours = padWithZeroes(hours, 2);
1659 							// Minutes
1660 							var minutes = "" + (absData % 60);
1661 							minutes = padWithZeroes(minutes, 2);
1662 
1663 							formattedString += prefix + hours + minutes;
1664 							break;
1665 					}
1666 				}
1667 				searchString = searchString.substr(result.index + result[0].length);
1668 			}
1669 			return formattedString;
1670 		};
1671 	})();

1678 	function PatternLayout(pattern) {
1679 		if (pattern) {
1680 			this.pattern = pattern;
1681 		} else {
1682 			this.pattern = PatternLayout.DEFAULT_CONVERSION_PATTERN;
1683 		}
1684 		this.customFields = [];
1685 	}
1686 
1687 	PatternLayout.TTCC_CONVERSION_PATTERN = "%r %p %c - %m%n";
1688 	PatternLayout.DEFAULT_CONVERSION_PATTERN = "%m%n";
1689 	PatternLayout.ISO8601_DATEFORMAT = "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss,SSS";
1690 	PatternLayout.DATETIME_DATEFORMAT = "dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss,SSS";
1691 	PatternLayout.ABSOLUTETIME_DATEFORMAT = "HH:mm:ss,SSS";
1692 
1693 	PatternLayout.prototype = new Layout();
1694 
1695 	PatternLayout.prototype.format = function(loggingEvent) {
1696 		var regex = /%(-?[0-9]+)?(\.?[0-9]+)?([acdfmMnpr%])(\{([^\}]+)\})?|([^%]+)/;
1697 		var formattedString = "";
1698 		var result;
1699 		var searchString = this.pattern;
1700 
1701 		// Cannot use regex global flag since it doesn't work with exec in IE5
1702 		while ((result = regex.exec(searchString))) {
1703 			var matchedString = result[0];
1704 			var padding = result[1];
1705 			var truncation = result[2];
1706 			var conversionCharacter = result[3];
1707 			var specifier = result[5];
1708 			var text = result[6];
1709 
1710 			// Check if the pattern matched was just normal text
1711 			if (text) {
1712 				formattedString += "" + text;
1713 			} else {
1714 				// Create a raw replacement string based on the conversion
1715 				// character and specifier
1716 				var replacement = "";
1717 				switch(conversionCharacter) {
1718 					case "a": // Array of messages
1719 					case "m": // Message
1720 						var depth = 0;
1721 						if (specifier) {
1722 							depth = parseInt(specifier, 10);
1723 							if (isNaN(depth)) {
1724 								handleError("PatternLayout.format: invalid specifier '" +
1725 									specifier + "' for conversion character '" + conversionCharacter +
1726 									"' - should be a number");
1727 								depth = 0;
1728 							}
1729 						}
1730 						var messages = (conversionCharacter === "a") ? loggingEvent.messages[0] : loggingEvent.messages;
1731 						for (var i = 0, len = messages.length; i < len; i++) {
1732 							if (i > 0 && (replacement.charAt(replacement.length - 1) !== " ")) {
1733 								replacement += " ";
1734 							}
1735 							if (depth === 0) {
1736 								replacement += messages[i];
1737 							} else {
1738 								replacement += formatObjectExpansion(messages[i], depth);
1739 							}
1740 						}
1741 						break;
1742 					case "c": // Logger name
1743 						var loggerName = loggingEvent.logger.name;
1744 						if (specifier) {
1745 							var precision = parseInt(specifier, 10);
1746 							var loggerNameBits = loggingEvent.logger.name.split(".");
1747 							if (precision >= loggerNameBits.length) {
1748 								replacement = loggerName;
1749 							} else {
1750 								replacement = loggerNameBits.slice(loggerNameBits.length - precision).join(".");
1751 							}
1752 						} else {
1753 							replacement = loggerName;
1754 						}
1755 						break;
1756 					case "d": // Date
1757 						var dateFormat = PatternLayout.ISO8601_DATEFORMAT;
1758 						if (specifier) {
1759 							dateFormat = specifier;
1760 							// Pick up special cases
1761 							if (dateFormat == "ISO8601") {
1762 								dateFormat = PatternLayout.ISO8601_DATEFORMAT;
1763 							} else if (dateFormat == "ABSOLUTE") {
1764 								dateFormat = PatternLayout.ABSOLUTETIME_DATEFORMAT;
1765 							} else if (dateFormat == "DATE") {
1766 								dateFormat = PatternLayout.DATETIME_DATEFORMAT;
1767 							}
1768 						}
1769 						// Format the date
1770 						replacement = (new SimpleDateFormat(dateFormat)).format(loggingEvent.timeStamp);
1771 						break;
1772 					case "f": // Custom field
1773 						if (this.hasCustomFields()) {
1774 							var fieldIndex = 0;
1775 							if (specifier) {
1776 								fieldIndex = parseInt(specifier, 10);
1777 								if (isNaN(fieldIndex)) {
1778 									handleError("PatternLayout.format: invalid specifier '" +
1779 										specifier + "' for conversion character 'f' - should be a number");
1780 								} else if (fieldIndex === 0) {
1781 									handleError("PatternLayout.format: invalid specifier '" +
1782 										specifier + "' for conversion character 'f' - must be greater than zero");
1783 								} else if (fieldIndex > this.customFields.length) {
1784 									handleError("PatternLayout.format: invalid specifier '" +
1785 										specifier + "' for conversion character 'f' - there aren't that many custom fields");
1786 								} else {
1787 									fieldIndex = fieldIndex - 1;
1788 								}
1789 							}
1790 							replacement = this.customFields[fieldIndex].value;
1791 						}
1792 						break;
1793 					case "n": // New line
1794 						replacement = newLine;
1795 						break;
1796 					case "p": // Level
1797 						replacement = loggingEvent.level.name;
1798 						break;
1799 					case "r": // Milliseconds since log4javascript startup
1800 						replacement = "" + loggingEvent.timeStamp.getDifference(applicationStartDate);
1801 						break;
1802 					case "%": // Literal % sign
1803 						replacement = "%";
1804 						break;
1805 					default:
1806 						replacement = matchedString;
1807 						break;
1808 				}
1809 				// Format the replacement according to any padding or
1810 				// truncation specified
1811 				var l;
1812 
1813 				// First, truncation
1814 				if (truncation) {
1815 					l = parseInt(truncation.substr(1), 10);
1816 					var strLen = replacement.length;
1817 					if (l < strLen) {
1818 						replacement = replacement.substring(strLen - l, strLen);
1819 					}
1820 				}
1821 				// Next, padding
1822 				if (padding) {
1823 					if (padding.charAt(0) == "-") {
1824 						l = parseInt(padding.substr(1), 10);
1825 						// Right pad with spaces
1826 						while (replacement.length < l) {
1827 							replacement += " ";
1828 						}
1829 					} else {
1830 						l = parseInt(padding, 10);
1831 						// Left pad with spaces
1832 						while (replacement.length < l) {
1833 							replacement = " " + replacement;
1834 						}
1835 					}
1836 				}
1837 				formattedString += replacement;
1838 			}
1839 			searchString = searchString.substr(result.index + result[0].length);
1840 		}
1841 		return formattedString;
1842 	};

1908 				window.console.warn(formattedMesage);
1909 			} else if (window.console.error && loggingEvent.level.isGreaterOrEqual(Level.ERROR)) {
1910 				window.console.error(formattedMesage);
1911 			} else {
1912 				window.console.log(formattedMesage);
1913 			}
1914 		}

2068 		// Internal functions
2069 		function sendAll() {
2070 			if (isSupported && enabled) {
2071 				sending = true;
2072 				var currentRequestBatch;
2073 				if (waitForResponse) {
2074 					// Send the first request then use this function as the callback once
2075 					// the response comes back
2076 					if (queuedRequests.length > 0) {
2077 						currentRequestBatch = queuedRequests.shift();
2078 						sendRequest(preparePostData(currentRequestBatch), sendAll);
2079 					} else {
2080 						sending = false;
2081 						if (timed) {
2082 							scheduleSending();
2083 						}
2084 					}
2085 				} else {
2086 					// Rattle off all the requests without waiting to see the response
2087 					while ((currentRequestBatch = queuedRequests.shift())) {
2088 						sendRequest(preparePostData(currentRequestBatch));
2089 					}
2090 					sending = false;
2091 					if (timed) {
2092 						scheduleSending();
2093 					}
2094 				}
2095 			}
2096 		}
2097 
2098 		this.sendAll = sendAll;

2100 		// Called when the window unloads. At this point we're past caring about
2101 		// waiting for responses or timers or incomplete batches - everything
2102 		// must go, now
2103 		function sendAllRemaining() {
2104 			if (isSupported && enabled) {
2105 				// Create requests for everything left over, batched as normal
2106 				var actualBatchSize = appender.getLayout().allowBatching() ? batchSize : 1;
2107 				var currentLoggingEvent;
2108 				var postData = "";
2109 				var batchedLoggingEvents = [];
2110 				while ((currentLoggingEvent = queuedLoggingEvents.shift())) {
2111 					batchedLoggingEvents.push(currentLoggingEvent);
2112 					if (queuedLoggingEvents.length >= actualBatchSize) {
2113 						// Queue this batch of log entries
2114 						queuedRequests.push(batchedLoggingEvents);
2115 						batchedLoggingEvents = [];
2116 					}
2117 				}
2118 				// If there's a partially completed batch, add it
2119 				if (batchedLoggingEvents.length > 0) {
2120 					queuedRequests.push(batchedLoggingEvents);
2121 				}
2122 				waitForResponse = false;
2123 				timed = false;
2124 				sendAll();
2125 			}
2126 		}
2127 
2128 		function preparePostData(batchedLoggingEvents) {
2129 			// Format the logging events
2130 			var formattedMessages = [];
2131 			var currentLoggingEvent;
2132 			var postData = "";
2133 			while ((currentLoggingEvent = batchedLoggingEvents.shift())) {
2134 				var currentFormattedMessage = appender.getLayout().format(currentLoggingEvent);
2135 				if (appender.getLayout().ignoresThrowable()) {
2136 					currentFormattedMessage += loggingEvent.getThrowableStrRep();
2137 				}
2138 				formattedMessages.push(currentFormattedMessage);
2139 			}
2140 			// Create the post data string
2141 			if (batchedLoggingEvents.length == 1) {
2142 				postData = formattedMessages.join("");
2143 			} else {
2144 				postData = appender.getLayout().batchHeader +
2145 					formattedMessages.join(appender.getLayout().batchSeparator) +
2146 					appender.getLayout().batchFooter;
2147 			}
2148 			postData = appender.getLayout().returnsPostData ? postData :
2149 				urlEncode(postVarName) + "=" + urlEncode(postData);
2150 			// Add the layout name to the post data
2151 			if (postData.length > 0) {
2152 				postData += "&";
2153 			}
2154 			return postData + "layout=" + urlEncode(appender.getLayout().toString());
2155 		}

2157 		function scheduleSending() {
2158 			setTimeout(sendAll, timerInterval);
2159 		}

2161 		function xmlHttpErrorHandler() {
2162 			var msg = "AjaxAppender: could not create XMLHttpRequest object. AjaxAppender disabled";
2163 			handleError(msg);
2164 			isSupported = false;
2165 			if (failCallback) {
2166 				failCallback(msg);
2167 			}

2170 		function sendRequest(postData, successCallback) {
2171 			try {
2172 				var xmlHttp = getXmlHttp(xmlHttpErrorHandler);
2173 				if (isSupported) {
2174 					if (xmlHttp.overrideMimeType) {
2175 						xmlHttp.overrideMimeType(appender.getLayout().getContentType());
2176 					}
2177 					xmlHttp.onreadystatechange = function() {
2178 						if (xmlHttp.readyState == 4) {
2179 							if (isHttpRequestSuccessful(xmlHttp)) {
2180 								if (requestSuccessCallback) {
2181 									requestSuccessCallback(xmlHttp);
2182 								}
2183 								if (successCallback) {
2184 									successCallback(xmlHttp);
2185 								}
2186 							} else {
2187 								var msg = "AjaxAppender.append: XMLHttpRequest request to URL " +
2188 									url + " returned status code " + xmlHttp.status;
2189 								handleError(msg);
2190 								if (failCallback) {
2191 									failCallback(msg);
2192 								}
2193 							}
2194 							xmlHttp.onreadystatechange = emptyFunction;
2195 							xmlHttp = null;
2196 						}
2197 					};
2198 					xmlHttp.open("POST", url, true);
2199 					try {
2200 						xmlHttp.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", "application/x-www-form-urlencoded");
2201 					} catch (headerEx) {
2202 						var msg = "AjaxAppender.append: your browser's XMLHttpRequest implementation" +
2203 							" does not support setRequestHeader, therefore cannot post data. AjaxAppender disabled";
2204 						handleError(msg);
2205 						isSupported = false;
2206 						if (failCallback) {
2207 							failCallback(msg);
2208 						}
2209 						return;
2210 					}
2211 					xmlHttp.send(postData);
2212 				}
2213 			} catch (ex) {
2214 				var errMsg = "AjaxAppender.append: error sending log message to " + url;
2215 				handleError(errMsg, ex);
2216 				isSupported = false;
2217 				if (failCallback) {
2218 					failCallback(errMsg + ". Details: " + getExceptionStringRep(ex));
2219 				}
2220 			}
2221 		}
2222 
2223 		this.append = function(loggingEvent) {
2224 			if (isSupported) {
2225 				if (!initialized) {
2226 					init();
2227 				}
2228 				queuedLoggingEvents.push(loggingEvent);
2229 				var actualBatchSize = this.getLayout().allowBatching() ? batchSize : 1;
2230 
2231 				if (queuedLoggingEvents.length >= actualBatchSize) {
2232 					var currentLoggingEvent;
2233 					var postData = "";
2234 					var batchedLoggingEvents = [];
2235 					while ((currentLoggingEvent = queuedLoggingEvents.shift())) {
2236 						batchedLoggingEvents.push(currentLoggingEvent);
2237 					}
2238 					// Queue this batch of log entries
2239 					queuedRequests.push(batchedLoggingEvents);
2240 
2241 					// If using a timer, the queue of requests will be processed by the
2242 					// timer function, so nothing needs to be done here.
2243 					if (!timed) {
2244 						if (!waitForResponse || (waitForResponse && !sending)) {
2245 							sendAll();
2246 						}
2247 					}
2248 				}
2249 			}
2250 		};

2253 			initialized = true;
2254 			// Add unload event to send outstanding messages
2255 			if (sendAllOnUnload) {
2256 				addEvent(window, "unload", sendAllRemaining);
2257 			}
2258 			// Start timer
2259 			if (timed) {
2260 				scheduleSending();
2261 			}
2262 		}
2263 	}

2288 	function setCookie(name, value, days, path) {
2289 	    var expires;
2290 	    path = path ? "; path=" + path : "";
2291 		if (days) {
2292 			var date = new Date();
2293 			date.setTime(date.getTime() + (days * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));
2294 			expires = "; expires=" + date.toGMTString();
2295 		} else {
2296 		    expires = "";
2297 	    }
2298 		document.cookie = escape(name) + "=" + escape(value) + expires + path;
2299 	}

2301 	function getCookie(name) {
2302 		var nameEquals = escape(name) + "=";
2303 		var ca = document.cookie.split(";");
2304 		for (var i = 0, len = ca.length; i < len; i++) {
2305 			var c = ca[i];
2306 			while (c.charAt(0) === " ") {
2307 			    c = c.substring(1, c.length);
2308 			}
2309 			if (c.indexOf(nameEquals) === 0) {
2310 			    return unescape(c.substring(nameEquals.length, c.length));
2311 	        }
2312 		}
2313 		return null;
2314 	}

3487 '			function Search(searchTerm, isRegex, searchRegex, isCaseSensitive) {',

3495 '			Search.prototype = {',
3496 '				hasMatches: function() {',
3497 '					return this.matches.length > 0;',
3498 '				},',
3499 '',
3500 '				hasVisibleMatches: function() {',
3501 '					if (this.hasMatches()) {',
3502 '						for (var i = 0; i < this.matches.length; i++) {',
3503 '							if (this.matches[i].isVisible()) {',
3504 '								return true;',

3509 '				},',

3512 '					var entryText = String(logEntry.formattedMessage);',
3513 '					var matchesSearch = false;',
3514 '					if (this.isRegex) {',
3515 '						matchesSearch = this.searchRegex.test(entryText);',
3516 '					} else if (this.isCaseSensitive) {',
3517 '						matchesSearch = (entryText.indexOf(this.searchTerm) > -1);',
3518 '					} else {',
3519 '						matchesSearch = (entryText.toLowerCase().indexOf(this.searchTerm.toLowerCase()) > -1);',
3520 '					}',
3521 '					return matchesSearch;',
3522 '				},',
3523 '',
3524 '				getNextVisibleMatchIndex: function() {',
3525 '					for (var i = currentMatchIndex + 1; i < this.matches.length; i++) {',
3526 '						if (this.matches[i].isVisible()) {',
3527 '							return i;',
3528 '						}',
3529 '					}',
3530 '					// Start again from the first match',
3531 '					for (i = 0; i <= currentMatchIndex; i++) {',
3532 '						if (this.matches[i].isVisible()) {',
3533 '							return i;',
3534 '						}',
3535 '					}',
3536 '					return -1;',
3537 '				},',

3540 '					for (var i = currentMatchIndex - 1; i >= 0; i--) {',
3541 '						if (this.matches[i].isVisible()) {',
3542 '							return i;',
3543 '						}',
3544 '					}',
3545 '					// Start again from the last match',
3546 '					for (var i = this.matches.length - 1; i >= currentMatchIndex; i--) {',
3547 '						if (this.matches[i].isVisible()) {',
3548 '							return i;',
3549 '						}',
3550 '					}',
3551 '					return -1;',
3552 '				},',
3553 '',

3555 '					var doesMatch = this.match(logEntry);',
3556 '					if (doesMatch) {',

3558 '						logEntry.setSearchMatch(true);',
3559 '						var logEntryContent;',
3560 '						var wrappedLogEntryContent;',
3561 '						var searchTermReplacementStartTag = "<span class=\\\"searchterm\\\">";',
3562 '						var searchTermReplacementEndTag = "<" + "/span>";',
3563 '						var preTagName = isIe ? "pre" : "span";',
3564 '						var preStartTag = "<" + preTagName + " class=\\\"pre\\\">";',
3565 '						var preEndTag = "<" + "/" + preTagName + ">";',
3566 '						var startIndex = 0;',
3567 '						var searchIndex, matchedText, textBeforeMatch;',
3568 '						if (this.isRegex) {',
3569 '							var flags = this.isCaseSensitive ? "g" : "gi";',
3570 '							var capturingRegex = new RegExp("(" + this.searchRegex.source + ")", flags);',
3571 '',
3572 '							// Replace the search term with temporary tokens for the start and end tags',
3573 '							var rnd = ("" + Math.random()).substr(2);',
3574 '							var startToken = "%%s" + rnd + "%%";',
3575 '							var endToken = "%%e" + rnd + "%%";',
3576 '							logEntryContent = logEntry.formattedMessage.replace(capturingRegex, startToken + "$1" + endToken);',
3577 '',
3578 '							// Escape the HTML to get rid of angle brackets',
3579 '							logEntryContent = escapeHtml(logEntryContent);',
3580 '',
3581 '							// Substitute the proper HTML back in for the search match',
3582 '							var result;',
3583 '							var searchString = logEntryContent;',
3584 '							logEntryContent = "";',
3585 '							wrappedLogEntryContent = "";',
3586 '							while ((searchIndex = searchString.indexOf(startToken, startIndex)) > -1) {',
3587 '								var endTokenIndex = searchString.indexOf(endToken, searchIndex);',
3588 '								matchedText = searchString.substring(searchIndex + startToken.length, endTokenIndex);',
3589 '								textBeforeMatch = searchString.substring(startIndex, searchIndex);',
3590 '								logEntryContent += preStartTag + textBeforeMatch + preEndTag;',
3591 '								logEntryContent += searchTermReplacementStartTag + preStartTag + matchedText +',
3592 '									preEndTag + searchTermReplacementEndTag;',
3593 '								if (isIe) {',
3594 '									wrappedLogEntryContent += textBeforeMatch + searchTermReplacementStartTag +',
3595 '										matchedText + searchTermReplacementEndTag;',
3596 '								}',
3597 '								startIndex = endTokenIndex + endToken.length;',
3598 '							}',
3599 '							logEntryContent += preStartTag + searchString.substr(startIndex) + preEndTag;',
3600 '							if (isIe) {',
3601 '								wrappedLogEntryContent += searchString.substr(startIndex);',
3602 '							}',
3603 '						} else {',
3604 '							logEntryContent = "";',
3605 '							wrappedLogEntryContent = "";',
3606 '							var searchTermReplacementLength = searchTermReplacementStartTag.length +',
3607 '								this.searchTerm.length + searchTermReplacementEndTag.length;',

4894 			this.evalCommandAndAppend = function(expr) {
4895 				var commandReturnValue = { appendResult: true, isError: false };
4896 				var commandOutput = "";
4897 				// Evaluate the command
4898 				try {
4899 					var result, i;
4900 					// The next three lines constitute a workaround for IE. Bizarrely, iframes seem to have no
4901 					// eval method on the window object initially, but once execScript has been called on
4902 					// it once then the eval method magically appears. See http://www.thismuchiknow.co.uk/?p=25
4903 					if (!commandWindow.eval && commandWindow.execScript) {
4904 						commandWindow.execScript("null");
4905 					}
4906 
4907 					var commandLineFunctionsHash = {};
4908 					for (i = 0, len = commandLineFunctions.length; i < len; i++) {
4909 						commandLineFunctionsHash[commandLineFunctions[i][0]] = commandLineFunctions[i][1];
4910 					}
4911 
4912 					// Keep an array of variables that are being changed in the command window so that they
4913 					// can be restored to their original values afterwards
4914 					var objectsToRestore = [];
4915 					var addObjectToRestore = function(name) {
4916 						objectsToRestore.push([name, commandWindow[name]]);
4917 					};
4918 
4919 					addObjectToRestore("appender");
4920 					commandWindow.appender = appender;
4921 
4922 					addObjectToRestore("commandReturnValue");
4923 					commandWindow.commandReturnValue = commandReturnValue;
4924 
4925 					addObjectToRestore("commandLineFunctionsHash");
4926 					commandWindow.commandLineFunctionsHash = commandLineFunctionsHash;
4927 
4928 					var addFunctionToWindow = function(name) {
4929 						addObjectToRestore(name);
4930 						commandWindow[name] = function() {
4931 							return this.commandLineFunctionsHash[name](appender, arguments, commandReturnValue);
4932 						};
4933 					};
4934 
4935 					for (i = 0, len = commandLineFunctions.length; i < len; i++) {
4936 						addFunctionToWindow(commandLineFunctions[i][0]);
4937 					}
4938 
4939 					// Another bizarre workaround to get IE to eval in the global scope
4940 					if (commandWindow === window && commandWindow.execScript) {
4941 						addObjectToRestore("evalExpr");
4942 						addObjectToRestore("result");
4943 						window.evalExpr = expr;
4944 						commandWindow.execScript("window.result=eval(window.evalExpr);");
4945 						result = window.result;
4946  					} else {
4947  						result = commandWindow.eval(expr);
4948  					}
4949 					commandOutput = isUndefined(result) ? result : formatObjectExpansion(result, commandLineObjectExpansionDepth);
4950 
4951 					// Restore variables in the command window to their original state
4952 					for (i = 0, len = objectsToRestore.length; i < len; i++) {
4953 						commandWindow[objectsToRestore[i][0]] = objectsToRestore[i][1];
4954 					}
4955 				} catch (ex) {
4956 					commandOutput = "Error evaluating command: " + getExceptionStringRep(ex);
4957 					commandReturnValue.isError = true;
4958 				}
4959 				// Append command output
4960 				if (commandReturnValue.appendResult) {
4961 					var message = ">>> " + expr;
4962 					if (!isUndefined(commandOutput)) {
4963 						message += newLine + commandOutput;
4964 					}
4965 					var level = commandReturnValue.isError ? Level.ERROR : Level.INFO;
4966 					var loggingEvent = new LoggingEvent(null, new Date(), level, [message], null);
4967 					var mainLayout = this.getLayout();
4968 					this.setLayout(commandLayout);
4969 					this.append(loggingEvent);
4970 					this.setLayout(mainLayout);
4971 				}
4972 			};

5494 	function padWithSpaces(str, len) {
5495 		if (str.length < len) {
5496 			var spaces = [];
5497 			var numberOfSpaces = Math.max(0, len - str.length);
5498 			for (var i = 0; i < numberOfSpaces; i++) {
5499 				spaces[i] = " ";
5500 			}
5501 			str += spaces.join("");
5502 		}
5503 		return str;
5504 	}

5507 		function dir(obj) {
5508 			var maxLen = 0;
5509 			// Obtain the length of the longest property name
5510 			for (var p in obj) {
5511 				maxLen = Math.max(toStr(p).length, maxLen);
5512 			}
5513 			// Create the nicely formatted property list
5514 			var propList = [];
5515 			for (p in obj) {
5516 				var propNameStr = "  " + padWithSpaces(toStr(p), maxLen + 2);
5517 				var propVal;
5518 				try {
5519 					propVal = splitIntoLines(toStr(obj[p])).join(padWithSpaces(newLine, maxLen + 6));
5520 				} catch (ex) {
5521 					propVal = "[Error obtaining property. Details: " + getExceptionMessage(ex) + "]";
5522 				}
5523 				propList.push(propNameStr + propVal);
5524 			}
5525 			return propList.join(newLine);
5526 		}

5549 		// Create and return an XHTML string from the node specified
5550 		function getXhtml(rootNode, includeRootNode, indentation, startNewLine, preformatted) {
5551 			includeRootNode = (typeof includeRootNode == "undefined") ? true : (includeRootNode ? true : false);
5552 			if (typeof indentation != "string") {
5553 				indentation = "";
5554 			}
5555 			startNewLine = startNewLine ? true : false;
5556 			preformatted = preformatted ? true : false;

5560 				return ((node.nodeType == nodeTypes.TEXT_NODE) && /^[ \t\r\n]*$/.test(node.nodeValue));
5561 			}

5563 			function fixAttributeValue(attrValue) {
5564 				return attrValue.toString().replace(/\&/g, "&").replace(/</g, "<").replace(/\"/g, """);
5565 			}

5567 			function getStyleAttributeValue(el) {
5568 				var stylePairs = el.style.cssText.split(";");
5569 				var styleValue = "";
5570 				var isFirst = true;
5571 				for (var j = 0, len = stylePairs.length; j < len; j++) {
5572 					var nameValueBits = stylePairs[j].split(":");
5573 					var props = [];
5574 					if (!/^\s*$/.test(nameValueBits[0])) {
5575 						props.push(trim(nameValueBits[0]).toLowerCase() + ":" + trim(nameValueBits[1]));
5576 					}
5577 					styleValue = props.join(";");
5578 				}
5579 				return styleValue;
5580 			}

5582 			function getNamespace(el) {
5583 				if (el.prefix) {
5584 					return el.prefix;
5585 				} else if (el.outerHTML) {
5586 					var regex = new RegExp("<([^:]+):" + el.tagName + "[^>]*>", "i");
5587 					if (regex.test(el.outerHTML)) {
5588 						return RegExp.$1.toLowerCase();
5589 					}
5590 				}
5591                 return "";
5592 			}
5593 
5594 			var lt = "<";
5595 			var gt = ">";
5596 
5597 			if (includeRootNode && rootNode.nodeType != nodeTypes.DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE) {
5598 				switch (rootNode.nodeType) {
5599 					case nodeTypes.ELEMENT_NODE:
5600 						var tagName = rootNode.tagName.toLowerCase();
5601 						xhtml = startNewLine ? newLine + indentation : "";
5602 						xhtml += lt;
5603 						// Allow for namespaces, where present
5604 						var prefix = getNamespace(rootNode);
5605 						var hasPrefix = prefix ? true : false;
5606 						if (hasPrefix) {
5607 							xhtml += prefix + ":";
5608 						}
5609 						xhtml += tagName;
5610 						for (i = 0, len = rootNode.attributes.length; i < len; i++) {
5611 							var currentAttr = rootNode.attributes[i];
5612 							// Check the attribute is valid.
5613 							if (!	currentAttr.specified ||
5614 									currentAttr.nodeValue === null ||
5615 									currentAttr.nodeName.toLowerCase() === "style" ||
5616 									typeof currentAttr.nodeValue !== "string" ||
5617 									currentAttr.nodeName.indexOf("_moz") === 0) {
5618 								continue;
5619 							}
5620 							xhtml += " " + currentAttr.nodeName.toLowerCase() + "=\"";
5621 							xhtml += fixAttributeValue(currentAttr.nodeValue);
5622 							xhtml += "\"";
5623 						}
5624 						// Style needs to be done separately as it is not reported as an
5625 						// attribute in IE
5626 						if (rootNode.style.cssText) {
5627 							var styleValue = getStyleAttributeValue(rootNode);
5628 							if (styleValue !== "") {
5629 								xhtml += " style=\"" + getStyleAttributeValue(rootNode) + "\"";
5630 							}
5631 						}
5632 						if (array_contains(emptyElements, tagName) ||
5633 								(hasPrefix && !rootNode.hasChildNodes())) {
5634 							xhtml += "/" + gt;
5635 						} else {
5636 							xhtml += gt;
5637 							// Add output for childNodes collection (which doesn't include attribute nodes)
5638 							var childStartNewLine = !(rootNode.childNodes.length === 1 &&
5639 								rootNode.childNodes[0].nodeType === nodeTypes.TEXT_NODE);
5640 							var childPreformatted = array_contains(preFormattedElements, tagName);
5641 							for (var i = 0, len = rootNode.childNodes.length; i < len; i++) {
5642 								xhtml += getXhtml(rootNode.childNodes[i], true, indentation + indentationUnit,
5643 									childStartNewLine, childPreformatted);
5644 							}
5645 							// Add the end tag
5646 							var endTag = lt + "/" + tagName + gt;
5647 							xhtml += childStartNewLine ? newLine + indentation + endTag : endTag;
5648 						}
5649 						return xhtml;
5650 					case nodeTypes.TEXT_NODE:
5651 						if (isWhitespace(rootNode)) {
5652 							xhtml = "";
5653 						} else {
5654 							if (preformatted) {
5655 								xhtml = rootNode.nodeValue;
5656 							} else {
5657 								// Trim whitespace from each line of the text node
5658 								var lines = splitIntoLines(trim(rootNode.nodeValue));
5659 								var trimmedLines = [];
5660 								for (var i = 0, len = lines.length; i < len; i++) {
5661 									trimmedLines[i] = trim(lines[i]);
5662 								}
5663 								xhtml = trimmedLines.join(newLine + indentation);
5664 							}
5665 							if (startNewLine) {
5666 								xhtml = newLine + indentation + xhtml;
5667 							}
5668 						}
5669 						return xhtml;
5670 					case nodeTypes.CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
5671 						return "<![CDA" + "TA[" + rootNode.nodeValue + "]" + "]>" + newLine;
5672 					case nodeTypes.DOCUMENT_NODE:
5673 						xhtml = "";
5674 						// Add output for childNodes collection (which doesn't include attribute nodes)
5675 						for (var i = 0, len = rootNode.childNodes.length; i < len; i++) {
5676 							xhtml += getXhtml(rootNode.childNodes[i], true, indentation);
5677 						}
5678 						return xhtml;
5679 					default:
5680 						return "";
5681 				}
5682 			} else {
5683 				xhtml = "";
5684 				// Add output for childNodes collection (which doesn't include attribute nodes)
5685 				for (var i = 0, len = rootNode.childNodes.length; i < len; i++) {
5686 					xhtml += getXhtml(rootNode.childNodes[i], true, indentation + indentationUnit);
5687 				}
5688 				return xhtml;
5689 			}
5690 		}
